SEARCH

All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
ActiveActor
Abstract class representing an active actor in the game.
ActiveActorDestructible
Abstract class representing an active actor that can be destroyed.
Boss
Represents the boss plane in the game with movement, shields, and firing capabilities.
BossProjectile
BossProjectile represents the projectiles fired by the boss.
Controller
Controller class orchestrates the game's lifecycle and setup.
DefaultProjectileFiringBehavior
DefaultProjectileFiringBehavior implements the behavior for firing a single projectile in a straight line.
Destructible
The Destructible interface represents objects that can take damage and be destroyed.
EnemyPlane
EnemyPlane represents an enemy aircraft in the game.
EnemyProjectile
EnemyProjectile represents projectiles fired by enemy planes.
EnemySpawner
EnemySpawner is responsible for handling the logic of spawning enemy units in a game level.
ErrorHandler
ErrorHandler utility class handles error reporting and displays alerts to the user.
EventListener
EventListener class listens for property changes and triggers appropriate actions, such as transitioning to the next level in the game.
FighterPlane
Abstract class representing a fighter plane in the game.
GameOverImage
GameOverImage represents the "Game Over" screen image displayed when the player loses the game.
GameProgressManager
GameProgressManager is responsible for managing the player's progress in the game.
Health
Health class manages the health of an object.
HeartDisplay
HeartDisplay represents the UI component for displaying the player's health using heart icons.
HitboxRenderer
HitboxRenderer is a utility class for rendering hitboxes in the game.
HowToPlayWindow
Class responsible for displaying the "How to Play" window.
KillCountTracker
KillCountTracker is a utility class for tracking the number of kills made by a specific actor (e.g., UserPlane) in the game.
LevelBoss
LevelBoss represents the boss level in the game.
LevelManager
LevelManager class is responsible for managing level transitions in the game.
LevelOne
LevelOne represents the first level of the game.
LevelParent
LevelParent is an abstract class that serves as the foundation for all game levels.
LevelTwo
LevelTwo represents the second level of the game.
LevelView
LevelView manages the visual elements of a game level, including the heart display, score display, win screen, and game over screen.
LevelViewBoss
LevelViewBoss is a specialized view class for displaying elements specific to the boss level.
Main
The Main class serves as the entry point for the Sky Battle game.
MainMenu
Main menu for the Space Battle application.
MovementPattern
Manages the movement pattern for the boss.
PauseMenu
The PauseMenu class represents the user interface displayed when the game is paused.
Projectile
Projectile is an abstract class representing a general projectile in the game.
ProjectileFiringBehavior
Interface for defining projectile firing behavior.
ShieldImage
ShieldImage represents the visual appearance of a shield in the game.
ShieldManager
Manages the shield state for the boss, including activation and deactivation logic.
StraightProjectile
StraightProjectile represents a projectile that moves in a straight line.
UserPlane
UserPlane represents the player's aircraft in the game.
UserProjectile
UserProjectile represents the projectiles fired by the player's plane.
WinImage
WinImage represents the visual display of a "You Win" screen in the game.
